               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾāmra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus” (fols. 3ra-118rb)&#xD; I-1)
                     Introduction (fols. 3ra-9vb) &#xD; - On John the Evangelist as the author of
                     the book; on the creation and the fall of the angels (fols. 3ra-6rb) &#xD; -
                     Story of the family of Adam (fols. 6rb-9vb)&#xD; I-2) Taʾāmra ʾIyasus “Miracles
                     of Jesus”: 48 miracles (fols. 9vb-118rb)&#xD; &#xD; Additio 1;
                     colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The miracles 1-31 are numbered. The miracles (10) on fols. 8<ref type="mss" corresp="ES1ra118">1ra-118</ref>vb are not numbered.</note>
                     <note>The first miracle (<locus target="#9vb">9vb</locus> l.9-11va l.5) is
                        incorporated into Text I-1, introduced with the word kǝfl “part”, and
                        numbered as miracle 1.</note>
                     <note>On <locus from="57ra" to="73vb">57ra-73vb</locus>, 77rb-81ra the miracles
                        are introduced with the word kǝfl “part” and they are not numbered.</note>
                     <note>The miracle on <locus from="73vb" to="77rb">73vb-77rb</locus> is
                        introduced with the word mǝʿraf “chapter” and it is not numbered.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                     <locus target="#3r">3r</locus> l.1-10: በስመ፡”…ንዌጥን፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ተአምሪሁ፡ ለእግዚእነ፡ ወአምላክነ፡
                     ወመድኃኒነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ በ፸፻ወ፪፻፴፡ ወአሚሩ፡ ዓመተ፡ ዓለም፡ በዘመነ፡ ሉቃስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ አመ፡ ፳ወ፭፡
                     ለመስከረም፡ በሠረቀ፡ ሌሊት፡ ወ፬፡ በሠረቀ፡ መዓልት፡ በዕለተ፡ ዓርብ፡ በ፲ [<locus target="#3rb">3rb</locus>] ቱ፡ ዓመቱ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ለንጉሠ፡ ነገሥት፡ ጊጋር፡ ዘተሰምየ፡ በጸጋ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ሣህሉ፡
                     ወምሕረቱ፡ ለእግዚእነ፡ ወአምላክነ፡ ወመድኃኒነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወስእለተ፡ እሙ፡ የሀሉ፡ ምስለ፡ ገብሩ ወምስለ፡
                     ጸሐፊሁ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን:: The colophon is placed before the beginning
                     of the text.&#xD; According to the colophon the scribe, Gabra Māryām (hand a),
                     began to write the Ms. in 7230 year of the world (= 1830 A.D.), in the year of
                     Luke the Evangelist, on 25 of Maskaram, on Friday, in the 10th year of the
                     reign of King of Kings Gigar (r. 1821-26, 1826-30, s. EAE vol. 2, p. 792). The
                     blank for the name of a commissioner has been left unfilled. </colophon>
               </msContents>
